description: If you show any symptoms related to COVID-19, please contact 10655 immediately. The following hospitals have been allocated as of now to treat COVID-19 patients.
Institute provides free health care services, including investigations and medication to the patients.
Critical patients are treated in the IMCU, ICU, CCU, PICU, HDU and Cathlab while burns cases are treated in the BCU.
A blood bank is a center where blood gathered as a result of blood donation is stored and preserved for later use in blood transfusion.
A laboratory (lab) test is a procedure in which a health care provider takes a sample of your blood, urine, other bodily fluid, or body tissue to get information about your health.
